20developments%20from%20across%20the%20world%20here%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Turns%20out%20no%20one%20can%20compete%20with%20Elon%20Musk's%20Twitter%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20twitter%20bird%20with%20worms%20in%20its%20mouth%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671abe9801ea6d83dee3f81b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbout%20three%20weeks%20after%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-donald-trump-support-reflects-business-approach-tesla-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20bought%20Twitter%20in%20October%202022%2C%20%23RIPTwitter%20started%20trending.%20Musk%20had%20gutted%20the%20staff%2C%20and%20more%20workers%20quit%20when%20he%20gave%20them%20an%20ultimatum%3A%20Work%20%26quot%3Bhardcore%26quot%3B%20hours%20or%20leave.%20With%20the%20platform%20on%20the%20brink%2C%20its%20users%20held%20a%20funeral.%20They%20spent%20the%20evening%20saying%20goodbye%20to%20their%20followers%2C%20shitposting%20on%20the%20%23hellsite%20for%20the%20last%20time%2C%20and%20rounding%20up%20the%20best%20and%20worst%20tweets%20they%20had%20saved%20in%20the%20platform's%2016-year%20history.%20They%20were%20somber%2C%20giddy%2C%20and%20anxious%20about%20the%20future%20of%20online%20dialogue.%20It%20seemed%20certain%20that%20a%20competitor%20would%20rise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERight%20then%2C%20Gabor%20Cselle%2C%20a%20former%20director%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-gemini-ai-layoffs-innovation-boring-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGoogle%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20employee%20at%20Twitter%2C%20was%20working%20on%20a%20rival%20app.%20First%20called%20T2%20and%20later%20Pebble%2C%20the%20goal%20was%20to%20make%20a%20trustworthy%2C%20safe%20site%20to%20fill%20the%20gap%20left%20by%20Twitter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECselle%20was%20far%20from%20alone.%20As%20the%20bird%20app's%20outlook%20grew%20more%20bleak%2C%20several%20alternative%20conversation%20platforms%20hatched%3A%20Narwhal%2C%20Spoutible%2C%20Spill%2C%20Post%2C%20and%20Cohost%20among%20them.%20In%20July%202023%2C%20Meta%20tried%20to%20seize%20the%20moment%20by%20launching%20Threads.%20Twitter%20cofounder%20Jack%20Dorsey%20tried%20to%20fix%20what%20he%20saw%20as%20Twitter's%20wrongs%20by%20launching%20Bluesky.%20(He%20quit%20in%20May%202024%2C%20saying%20the%20platform%20was%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-dorsey-bluesky-twiiter-nostr-interview-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Eliterally%20repeating%20all%20the%20mistakes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3B%20Twitter%20had%20made.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Twitter%20continued%20to%20teeter.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-tells-advertises-get-lost-twitter-dealbook-summit2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMusk%20told%20advertisers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%26quot%3Bgo%20fuck%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20abandoned%20most%20content%20moderation%2C%20and%20infamously%20changed%20the%20logo%20from%20a%20friendly%20blue%20bird%20to%20a%20cold%20X.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year%2C%20The%20Verge%20published%20a%20news%20package%20declaring%20that%202023%20would%20go%20down%20as%20%26quot%3BThe%20Year%20Twitter%20Died.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20two%20years%20after%20Musk%20took%20over%2C%20the%20platform%20is%20still%20the%20room%20where%20it%20happens.%20Misinformation%20has%20skyrocketed%20and%20growth%20has%20stagnated%3B%20the%20market-intelligence%20firm%20Sensor%20Tower%20says%20its%20number%20of%20active%20daily%20users%20dropped%20by%2028%25%20from%20October%202022%20to%20September%202024%20while%20Threads'%20users%20have%20grown.%20But%20when%20big%20news%20hits%2C%20like%20a%20major%20sporting%20event%20or%20a%20sitting%20president's%20decision%20to%20drop%20out%20of%20the%20race%20or%20the%20attempted%20assassination%20of%20a%20former%20president%2C%20X%20is%20where%20the%20conversation%20erupts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20Twitters'%20upstart%20challengers%20have%20folded.%20I%20talked%20to%20several%20founders%20about%20what%20they%20learned%20trying%20to%20compete%20with%20Musk%2C%20and%20the%20state%20of%20civil%20discussion%20online.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI%20sort%20of%20misread%20that%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20Cselle%20says%20today.%20He%20thought%20all%20those%20mourners%20wanted%20something%20that%20was%20just%20like%20Twitter%20but%20that%20would%20reliably%20work%20%E2%80%94%20somewhere%20without%20excessive%20trolling%20and%20hate%20speech%20and%20deepfakes.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20%23RIPTwitter%20was%20about%2C%20in%20retrospect%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20was%20a%20panicked%20%26quot%3Bsense%20of%20'I%20might%20lose%20my%20status%20and%20my%20following%20and%20my%20handle%20and%20all%20of%20this%20network%20I've%20built%20up.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECselle%20says%20he's%20learned%20that%20for%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20%26quot%3Btrust%20and%20safety%20is%20a%20secondary%20value%20proposition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt%20becomes%20important%20to%20you%20as%20a%20user%20%E2%80%94%20imminently%20and%20immediately%20important%20%E2%80%94%20once%20something%20goes%20really%20bad%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20But%20he's%20learned%20that%20people%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20join%20a%20new%20space%20that%20is%20otherwise%20empty%20for%20it.%20You%20can't%20start%20a%20Twitter%20alternative%20by%20saying%2C%20'We%20want%20to%20be%20the%20new%20public%20square.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPebble%20got%20about%2020%2C000%20registered%20users%20before%20stagnating%20and%20shutting%20down%20in%20November%202023.%20It%20lives%20on%20as%20a%20smaller%20server%20on%20Mastodon%2C%20which%20itself%20peaked%20at%202.5%20million%20active%20users%20in%20December%202022%20but%20is%20down%20to%20about%20865%2C000.%20Cohost%2C%20made%20by%20the%20Anti%20Software%20Software%20Club%20(which%20describes%20itself%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20not-for-profit%20software%20company%20that%20hates%20the%20software%20industry%26quot%3B)%2C%20said%20last%20month%20that%20it%20was%20running%20out%20of%20money%20and%20would%20become%20read-only%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Post%2C%20a%20platform%20%26quot%3Bbuilt%20for%20news%2C%26quot%3B%20launched%20in%20fall%202022%2C%20publishers%20like%20Politico%2C%20The%20Boston%20Globe%2C%20and%20Fortune%20signed%20up%2C%20and%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20joined%20the%20waitlist.%20Founded%20by%20former%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-waze%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWaze%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20CEO%20Noam%20Bardin%20and%20funded%20in%20part%20by%20Andreessen%20Horowitz%2C%20the%20idea%20was%20that%20people%20could%20pay%20small%20amounts%20to%20read%20individual%20news%20articles%20rather%20than%20subscribing%20to%20many%20outlets.%20%26quot%3BI%20believe%20the%20future%20newspaper%20is%20the%20feed%20and%20want%20to%20make%20it%20more%20civil%20for%20users%2C%20profitable%20for%20publishers%20and%20better%20for%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20Bardin%20said%20in%20a%20tweet%20announcing%20Post.%20But%20it%20shut%20down%20in%20April%202024%2C%20citing%20slow%20growth%20that%20gave%20it%20no%20path%20toward%20becoming%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20platform.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeveral%20of%20these%20alternative%20conversation%20platforms%20were%20born%20from%20a%20similar%20ethos%2C%20searching%20to%20fix%20the%20chaos%20and%20bile%20that%20legacy%20social%20media%20had%20incentivized.%20Narwhal%2C%20backed%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaurene-powell-jobs-net-worth-life-career-spending-habits-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ELaurene%20Powell%20Jobs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E'%20Emerson%20Collective%2C%20marketed%20itself%20as%20a%20platform%20for%20%26quot%3Bproductive%20discussions%20grounded%20in%20good%20faith.%26quot%3B%20It%20began%20as%20invite-only%2C%20and%20dialogue%20centered%20on%20topics%20of%20the%20day%20that%20Narwhal%20would%20determine%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20about%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20environment%2C%20politics%2C%20or%20tech.%20Nicholas%20Thompson%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20The%20Atlantic%20and%20a%20cofounder%20of%20Narwhal%2C%20says%20that%20while%20the%20conversations%20among%20the%20hundreds%20of%20users%20were%20substantive%20and%20engaging%2C%20Narwhal%20lacked%20Twitter's%20bite.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20also%20the%20tradeoff%2C%26quot%3B%20Thompson%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20there%20had%20been%20a%20way%20to%20make%20it%20more%20fun%20while%20also%20thoughtful%2C%20that%20would%20have%20been%20the%20road%20to%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20a%20few%20months%2C%20Narwhal%20pivoted%20to%20become%20an%20AI%20software-as-a-service%20platform%2C%20Speakeasy%20AI%2C%20which%20aimed%20to%20enable%20civil%2C%20engaging%20dialogue%20on%20other%20platforms.%20Thompson%20says%20the%20goal%20wasn't%20to%20replace%20Twitter%20but%20to%20fix%20toxicity%20online.%20He%20wanted%20to%20build%20something%20that%20Twitter%2C%20Reddit%2C%20or%20Facebook%20might%20use.%20The%20company%20didn't%20grow%20much%2C%20and%20in%20April%2C%20Speakeasy's%20tech%20was%20acquired%20by%20Amplica%20Labs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20Thompson%20says%20the%20civil%20conversations%20on%20Narwhal%20gave%20him%20hope.%20Social%20media%20is%20fracturing%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it's%20a%20leak%20rather%20than%20a%20flood.%20That%20gives%20people%20opportunities%20to%20find%20different%20communities%20or%20uses%20for%20social%20sites.%20A%20legacy%20platform%20like%20X%20or%20a%20large%20one%20like%20TikTok%2C%20have%20their%20advantages%2C%20too%2C%20and%20might%20become%20a%20crowded%20center%20for%20discussion%2C%20but%20users%20are%20left%20to%20the%20whims%20of%20its%20CEO.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20ton%20of%20power%20in%20whoever%20controls%26quot%3B%20a%20big%20social%20media%20platform%2C%20Thompson%20says.%20Last%20week%2C%20Musk%20shared%20an%20image%20edited%20to%20show%20an%20Atlantic%20story%20with%20the%20headline%20%26quot%3BTrump%20is%20literally%20Hitler.%26quot%3B%20The%20post%20has%20more%20than%2025%20million%20views.%20Musk%20hasn't%20deleted%20the%20tweet%2C%20though%20a%20community%20note%20posted%20below%20it%20clarifies%20that%20the%20headline%20is%20fabricated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20places%20where%20Twitter's%20former%20users%20went%20are%20still%20growing.%20Spill%2C%20a%20Black-owned%20social%20platform%2C%20has%20been%20downloaded%20more%20than%20half%20a%20million%20times.%20Like%20other%20Twitter%20alternatives%2C%20it%20set%20out%20to%20solve%20the%20problems%20with%20hate%20speech%20on%20big%20platforms.%20But%20its%20mission%20is%20broader%3A%20Its%20cofounder%20Alphonzo%20Terrell%20says%20that%20while%20the%20app%20is%20open%20to%20everyone%2C%20it%20prioritizes%20elevating%20minority%20communities%2C%20like%20Black%20and%20LGBTQ%2B%2C%20and%20protecting%20them%20from%20harassment%20and%20hate%20Spill%20has%20raised%20nearly%20%245%20million%20in%20pre-seed%20funding%2C%20with%20the%20actor%20Kerry%20Washington%20recently%20investing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpill%20uses%20large%20language%20models%20and%20AI%20for%20content%20moderation%2C%20Terrell%20tells%20me.%20As%20with%20Narwhal%2C%20its%20algorithm%20rewards%20positive%20posts.%20But%20there's%20still%20room%20for%20political%20discussion%3A%20When%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20announced%20this%20summer%20that%20he%20would%20not%20seek%20reelection%20and%20Vice%20President%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharris-closing-message-trump-john-kelly-fascist-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKamala%20Harris%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20became%20the%20presumptive%20Democratic%20nominee%2C%20Spill%20saw%20a%20flurry%20of%20activity%2C%20Terrell%20says.%20Black%20women%20on%20the%20platform%20in%20particular%20talked%20about%20preparing%20themselves%20for%20an%20onslaught%20of%20racism%20and%20misogyny%20as%20the%20result%20of%20Harris'%20rise.%20It's%20a%20more%20nuanced%20political%20conversation%20than%20what%20might%20trend%20on%20something%20like%20X%2C%20but%20it%20worked%20on%20Spill.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20need%20to%20code%20switch%26quot%3B%20on%20Spill%2C%20Terrell%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rush%20to%20become%20the%20next%20Twitter%20has%20slowed%20%E2%80%94%20though%20there's%20still%20a%20chance%20an%20alternative%20could%20become%20popular%20enough%20to%20replace%20it.%20Threads%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20lure%20advertisers%2C%20but%20culturally%20it%20hasn't%20proved%20the%20Twitter%20killer%20many%20thought%20it%20might%20be.%20A%20lot%20of%20these%20brand-safe%20or%20news-focused%20apps%20have%20tended%20to%20feel%20more%20like%20homework%20than%20recess%2C%20though%20Spill%20may%20be%20the%20exception%20for%20now.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20been%20on%20Twitter%20since%202010.%20Recently%20I've%20found%20it%20less%20useful%20for%20my%20work%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20but%20I'm%20still%20lurking.%20And%20early%20this%20month%2C%20when%20my%20beloved%20Phillies%20tanked%20their%20playoff%20chances%20spectacularly%2C%20I%20turned%20to%20X.%20The%20algorithm%20knew%20I%20cared%20about%20this%3B%20it%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20commiserate%20with%20fellow%20fans%20and%20look%20at%20memes%20and%20watch%20highlights%20from%20the%20one%20game%20where%20the%20team%20played%20well%20over%20and%20over%20and%20over%2C%20which%20I'll%20be%20doing%20until%20opening%20day%20in%202025.%20I%20wasn't%20engaging%20in%20elevated%2C%20thought-provoking%20dialogue%2C%20nor%20was%20I%20spreading%20misinformation%20or%20hate.%20I%20was%20doing%20something%20in%20the%20middle%20%E2%80%94%20something%20cathartic.%20It%20was%20just%20what%20I%20was%20looking%20for.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-x-elon-musk-startup-competitition-town-square-election-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730108761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-x-elon-musk-startup-competitition-town-square-election-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20Elon%20Musk%20took%20over%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20Twitter%20was%20pronounced%20dead.%20Many%20challengers%20assembled.%20Here's%20what%20they%20learned.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-x-elon-musk-startup-competitition-town-square-election-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20end%20of%20American%20careerism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223606%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20holding%20a%20ladder%20and%20walking%20away%20from%20others%20climbing%20ladders%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670d7a97a70318649281b780%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221803%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Yates%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELate%20last%20year%2C%20two%20of%20Zack's%20managers%20at%20the%20construction%20and%20engineering%20firm%20where%20he%20works%20pulled%20him%20aside.%20Congratulations%2C%20they%20said.%20You're%20getting%20promoted%20to%20be%20the%20head%20of%20the%20department.%20They%20told%20him%20the%20role%20would%20come%20with%20a%2010%25%20raise%20%E2%80%94%20or%20maybe%20even%20more.%20They%20thought%20they%20were%20rewarding%20him%20for%20all%20his%20great%20work.%20But%20the%20whole%20time%2C%20Zack%20had%20one%20thought%20on%20his%20mind%3A%20%3Cem%3EHow%20do%20I%20get%20out%20of%20this%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20liked%20his%20current%20role%20at%20the%20company%2C%20and%20he%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20running%20a%20whole%20team.%20Besides%2C%20becoming%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftruth-promotions-companies-picking-managers-wrong-new-study-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanager%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20require%20him%20to%20go%20into%20the%20office%20every%20day%2C%20the%20way%20he%20used%20to%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20%26quot%3BI%20get%20to%20see%20my%20kids%20so%20much%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BYou%20couldn't%20pay%20me%20enough%20to%20give%20that%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20his%20bosses%20it%20was%20a%20big%20change%20and%20promised%20to%20think%20it%20over.%20A%20few%20days%20later%2C%20much%20to%20their%20surprise%2C%20he%20turned%20it%20down.%20%26quot%3BI%20talked%20about%20this%20with%20my%20wife%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20this%20position%20is%20the%20correct%20fit%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20them.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20really%20happy%20with%20what%20I'm%20doing.%20I'm%20really%20good%20at%20what%20I'm%20doing%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburnout-women-executives-hustle-culture-girlboss-work-life-balance-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClimbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20once%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20American%20dream.%20But%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I've%20been%20hearing%20about%20people%20like%20Zack%20who%20no%20longer%20aspire%20to%20the%20fancy%20titles%2C%20corner%20offices%2C%20and%20bigger%20paychecks%20that%20come%20with%20a%20promotion.%20Many%20are%20trying%20to%20fly%20under%20the%20radar%2C%20desperately%20hoping%20they%20won't%20get%20a%20tap%20on%20the%20shoulder.%20Others%20are%20outright%20declining%20promotions%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20asking%20for%20a%20%3Cem%3Edemotion%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20a%20role%20with%20fewer%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20survey%20conducted%20by%20Randstad%2C%20a%20global%20human-resources%20consultancy%2C%20a%20whopping%2042%25%20of%20respondents%20in%20the%20United%20States%20said%20they%20don't%20want%20a%20promotion%20because%20they're%20happy%20where%20they%20are.%20That%20was%20higher%20than%20in%20countries%20that%20are%20known%20for%20being%20more%20laid%20back%20about%20work%2C%20like%20Italy%2C%20Spain%2C%20and%20New%20Zealand.%20Maybe%20that's%20why%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20young%20New%20Yorker%20struck%20a%20chord%20on%20TikTok%20when%20he%20vowed%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40aaronflarin%2Fvideo%2F7355249341054962990%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edescend%20the%20corporate%20ladder%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BSome%20people%20want%20to%20be%20a%20manager%2C%20and%20that's%20OK%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20deserves%20the%20opportunity%20to%20get%20chewed%20out%20by%20the%20CEO%20directly.%20But%20the%20only%20team%20I%20want%20to%20be%20responsible%20for%20is%20my%20plants.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20walking%20away%20from%20another%20man%20holding%20money%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670d7af76ac7b701e7caed7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222363%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Yates%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20away%20from%20career%20advancement%20is%20bewildering%20for%20bosses%2C%20who%20fought%20so%20hard%20to%20ascend%20the%20ranks%20themselves.%20Take%20Dell%2C%20whose%20executives%20thought%20they%20came%20up%20with%20an%20ingenious%20plan%20to%20get%20everyone%20back%20into%20the%20office.%20If%20employees%20didn't%20come%20in%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20the%20company%20announced%20in%20February%2C%20they%20would%20be%20ineligible%20for%20a%20promotion.%20The%20response%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-dell-workers-reject-return-to-office-hybrid-work-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDell's%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20collective%20shrug.%20Months%20after%20the%20directive%2C%20nearly%20half%20of%20employees%20were%20still%20remote%2C%20apparently%20happy%20to%20remain%20in%20their%20current%20roles%20as%20long%20as%20they%20could%20keep%20working%20from%20home.%20It%20was%20a%20clear%20sign%20that%20in%202024%2C%20promotions%20just%20aren't%20the%20incentive%20they%20used%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20stake%2C%20though%2C%20is%20something%20much%20larger%20than%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-workers-blast-strict-rto-mandate-five-days-week-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERTO%20wars%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20all%2C%20careerism%20has%20long%20played%20an%20essential%20role%20in%20building%20dynamic%20and%20successful%20companies.%20The%20prospect%20of%20becoming%20senior%20vice%20president%20is%20what%20drove%20so%20many%20white-collar%20professionals%20to%20give%20it%20their%20all%2C%20even%20in%20the%20face%20of%20long%20hours%2C%20soul-crushing%20meetings%2C%20and%20petty%20office%20politics.%20If%20the%20allure%20of%20promotions%20can%20no%20longer%20get%20everyone%20to%20work%20hard%2C%20what%20will%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dream%20of%20climbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20feels%20as%20old%20as%20America%20itself.%20But%20200%20years%20ago%2C%20there%20was%20no%20corporate%20ladder%20to%20climb.%20The%20original%20work%20ethic%20in%20America%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Protestant%20one%2C%20espoused%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20Benjamin%20Franklin%20%E2%80%94%20dates%20from%20a%20time%20when%20most%20Americans%20were%20self-employed%20as%20farmers%20and%20artisans.%20It%20was%20rooted%20in%20a%20rugged%20individualism%20that%20was%20skeptical%20of%20authority%20and%20hierarchies%2C%20fitting%20for%20a%20country%20founded%20on%20the%20idea%20of%20freedom%20from%20tyranny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20became%20a%20problem%20when%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%20arrived.%20Companies%20exploded%20in%20size%2C%20and%20more%20and%20more%20Americans%20found%20themselves%20working%20for%20someone%20else.%20In%201820%2C%2080%25%20of%20the%20workforce%20was%20self-employed.%20By%201870%2C%20that%20share%20had%20shrunk%20to%2033%25.%20By%201940%2C%20it%20was%2020%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20moral%20vision%20of%20American%20society%20had%20been%20based%20upon%20the%20image%20of%20the%20independent%2C%20self-employed%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20writes%20Shoshana%20Zuboff%2C%20a%20professor%20emeritus%20at%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20who%20has%20studied%20the%20history%20of%20work.%20%26quot%3BMany%20social%20critics%20feared%20that%20people%20would%20be%20less%20likely%20to%20work%20hard%20under%20the%20wage%20system%20and%2C%20even%20worse%2C%20that%20something%20in%20their%20very%20natures%20might%20change.%26quot%3B%20America%20was%20facing%20an%20identity%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20solution%20was%20to%20forge%20a%20whole%20new%20work%20ethic%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20celebrated%20the%20sprawling%20corporate%20hierarchies%20that%20were%20swallowing%20up%20most%20Americans.%20The%20ideal%20was%20no%20longer%20independence%20but%20%3Cem%3Einter%3C%2Fem%3Edependence%2C%20a%20willingness%20to%20be%20subsumed%20by%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20larger%20whole.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20managers%20of%20these%20new%20enterprises%20now%20needed%20to%20induce%20was%20obedience%20and%20efficiency%2C%26quot%3B%20writes%20Zuboff%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20the%20questioning%20stubborn%20ways%20of%20the%20autonomous%20crafts%20person%20idealized%20by%20the%20old%20work%20ethic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20%26quot%3Bcareer%20ethic%26quot%3B%20came%20with%20a%20carrot.%20By%20serving%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloyal%20soldiers%20for%20their%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20employees%20could%20expect%20to%20gain%20more%20prestige%2C%20better%20job%20security%2C%20and%20bigger%20salaries.%20Help%20the%20boss%2C%20professionals%20were%20told%2C%20and%20maybe%20you%20can%20%3Cem%3Ebecome%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20boss.%20The%20new%20ethic%20took%20hold%20among%20the%20managerial%20class%20in%20the%201950s.%20By%20the%201970s%2C%20it%20had%20spread%20to%20the%20entire%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHalf%20a%20century%20later%2C%20the%20careerist%20ethos%20is%20still%20the%20bible%20of%20the%20corporate%20workplace.%20Those%20who%20try%20to%20opt%20out%20risk%20getting%20blacklisted%20as%20weirdos%20or%20losers%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foverachievers-leaning-back-hustle-culture-coasting-employees-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20quitters%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20cracks%20are%20starting%20to%20appear%20in%20the%20system%3A%20Many%20people%2C%20it%20has%20become%20clear%2C%20are%20no%20longer%20willing%20to%20make%20the%20trade-offs%20required%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhustle-culture-got-america-addicted-to-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20hustle%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20the%20number%20of%20promotion%20deniers%20would%20likely%20be%20even%20higher%20if%20employees%20weren't%20worried%20about%20outing%20themselves%20as%20non-careerists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20guy%20I%20spoke%20with%2C%20a%20systems%20analyst%20I'll%20call%20James%2C%20is%20desperate%20to%20avoid%20the%20promotion%20his%20boss%20keeps%20hinting%20at.%20But%20he's%20worried%20about%20the%20consequences%20of%20turning%20it%20down.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20told%20him%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20go%20any%20further%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20he'll%20start%20passing%20me%20over%20for%20new%20ideas%20he%20has%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BFor%20some%20reason%2C%20in%20our%20society%20in%20America%2C%20that's%20kind%20of%20shunned.%20People%20are%20expected%20to%20want%20to%20keep%20climbing%20and%20climbing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EZack%2C%20who's%20in%20his%20early%2040s%2C%20was%20one%20of%20those%20people%20eager%20to%20keep%20climbing.%20As%20an%20apprentice%2C%20he%20dreamed%20of%20becoming%20a%20foreman.%20And%20once%20he%20became%20a%20foreman%2C%20he%20aspired%20for%20even%20higher%20positions.%20%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20run%20the%20largest%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20gain%20the%20most%20experience.%20I%20wanted%20to%20run%20the%20biggest%20crews.%26quot%3B%20Event