ll%20a%20big%20fucking%20lie.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20toe%20the%20company%20line%2C%20Zack%20quit.%20He%20found%20a%20job%20that%20didn't%20require%20him%20to%20be%20a%20manager%2C%20and%20took%20a%20%2420%2C000%20pay%20cut.%20Today%20he%20far%20prefers%20being%20an%20individual%20contributor%20who's%20free%20to%20focus%20on%20his%20own%20work%20%E2%80%94%20another%20reason%20he%20declined%20the%20promotion%20he%20was%20offered%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProfessionals%20younger%20than%20Zack%2C%20who's%20an%20elder%20millennial%2C%20appear%20to%20harbor%20an%20even%20stronger%20anti-advancement%20streak.%20In%20Randstad's%20survey%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-hot-jobs-tech-layoffs-healthcare-government-careers-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%3C%2Fa%3E%20respondents%20%E2%80%94%20those%20on%20the%20lowest%20rungs%20of%20the%20corporate%20ladder%2C%20earning%20the%20lowest%20salaries%20%E2%80%94%20were%20more%20likely%20than%20millennials%20or%20Gen%20Xers%20to%20agree%20with%20the%20statement%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20career%20progression.%26quot%3B%20In%20another%20survey%2C%20when%20Gallup%20asked%20people%20what's%20deterring%20them%20from%20seeking%20a%20position%20in%20senior%20leadership%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20were%20especially%20concerned%20with%20the%20long%20hours%20and%20round-the-clock%20demands%20that%20come%20with%20a%20job%20at%20the%20top.%20For%20a%20new%20generation%2C%20the%20age%20of%20American%20careerism%20is%20losing%20its%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOlder%20bosses%20might%20be%20inclined%20to%20chalk%20all%20this%20up%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20ambition%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sign%20that%20young%20people%20aren't%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20the%20effort.%20But%20I%20think%20it%20makes%20sense%20that%20the%20allure%20of%20career%20progression%20is%20fading%2C%20given%20how%20much%20the%20workplace%20has%20changed%20in%20recent%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20job%20security.%20Back%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20managers%20had%20nothing%20to%20fear%20from%20layoffs%2C%20because%20layoffs%20were%20basically%20unheard%20of.%20But%20today%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-managers-great-flattening-organization-meta-tech-layoffs-firing-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20a%20manager%3C%2Fa%3E%20puts%20a%20huge%20target%20on%20your%20back%2C%20because%20you%20earn%20a%20bigger%20salary.%20If%20you%20accept%20a%20promotion%20you%20might%20wind%20up%20being%20%3Cem%3Emore%20%3C%2Fem%3Eexpendable%2C%20rather%20than%20less.%20That%20elevated%20risk%20is%20the%20main%20reason%20that%20James%2C%20the%20systems%20analyst%2C%20plans%20to%20decline%20his%20impending%20promotion.%20%26quot%3BThey%20always%20do%20layoffs%20every%20two%20or%20three%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%20of%20his%20employer.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20come%20up%20higher%20on%20the%20list%20as%20someone%20who's%20getting%20paid%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20the%20dream%20of%20climbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20was%20probably%20never%20as%20great%20as%20it%20seemed%20to%20be.%20Often%2C%20people%20get%20promoted%20only%20to%20find%20themselves%20doing%20less%20of%20the%20meaningful%20work%20that%20attracted%20them%20to%20their%20profession%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20This%20is%20such%20a%20common%20problem%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20that%20management%20scholars%20have%20a%20special%20term%20for%20it%3A%20%3Cem%3Emanagerial%20blues%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It's%20the%20sad%20irony%20of%20corporate%20America%3A%20The%20higher%20up%20you%20go%2C%20the%20less%20fulfilling%20your%20job%20becomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20wants%20to%20be%20the%20VP%20or%20the%20partner%20with%20the%20corner%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Michel%20Anteby%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20organizations%20at%20Boston%20University.%20%26quot%3BThe%20imaginary%20is%20that%20life%20will%20be%20much%20better%20then.%20But%20in%20fact%20you%20might%20be%20losing%20out%20on%20something%20that's%20very%20meaningful%20to%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20can%20companies%20motivate%20employees%20to%20work%20hard%2C%20if%20promotions%20have%20lost%20their%20appeal%3F%20I%20posed%20that%20question%20to%20Zack.%20Given%20how%20betrayed%20he%20felt%20by%20his%20previous%20employer%2C%20I%20wondered%20if%20he%20no%20longer%20believes%20in%20dedicating%20himself%20to%20his%20job%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20potential%20rewards.%20But%20it%20turns%20out%20there%20are%20still%20plenty%20of%20things%20that%20motivate%20him.%20Getting%20to%20do%20interesting%20work.%20Having%20the%20autonomy%20to%20create%20his%20own%20schedule.%20Feeling%20like%20a%20trusted%20and%20valued%20member%20of%20the%20team.%20Being%20surrounded%20by%20peers%20who%20are%20great%20at%20what%20they%20do.%20Reporting%20to%20a%20manager%20who%20actually%2C%20in%20his%20words%2C%20%26quot%3Bgives%20a%20shit.%26quot%3B%20Those%20are%20the%20things%20that%20light%20a%20fire%20under%20him.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20work%20extra%2C%26quot%3B%20Zack%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20do%20try%20hard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20asked%20James%20what%20drives%20him%2C%20he%20said%20something%20similar.%20%26quot%3BI%20like%20my%20job%20and%20I%20want%20to%20keep%20getting%20better%20at%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20since%20I%20work%20at%20a%20hospital%2C%20I'm%20helping%20nurses%20and%20providers%20help%20their%20patients.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20important%20guidance%20here%20for%20employers.%20As%20the%20fever%20of%20careerism%20breaks%2C%20they%20can%20no%20longer%20rely%20on%20the%20shiny%20promise%20of%20a%20promotion%20to%20get%20people%20to%20devote%20themselves%20to%20roles%20that%20are%20boring%2C%20or%20toxic%2C%20or%20unfulfilling%2C%20or%20badly%20managed.%20But%20if%20they%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20jobs%20they%20offer%20are%20enjoyable%20and%20meaningful%20in%20th